      <h1 class='title'>Regulatory Impact Assessments</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 13 November 2003 vol 413 c24WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_24ws' title='Col. 24WS &mdash; HC Deb 13 November 2003 vol 413 c24WS' name='column_24ws' href='#column_24ws' rel='bookmark'>24WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0413P2_20031113_CWS_2'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-douglas-alexander' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0413P2_20031113_CWS_2' title='Link to this speech by Mr Douglas Alexander' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-douglas-alexander" title="Mr Douglas Alexander">The Minister for the Cabinet Office and Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster (Mr. Douglas Alexander)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The Government are committed to ensuring that regulations are necessary, give effective protection, balance cost and risk, are fair and command public confidence. In accordance with this, we require Departments to produce and publish RIAs for all regulatory proposals likely to have an impact on business, charities or voluntary bodies.</p><p>I have today presented to Parliament a Command Paper listing RIAs published between 1 January and 30 June 2003. Copies of those listed have been placed in the Libraries of both Houses. This is the 19th such Command Paper. </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
